- Execute the following rake task, to get a list of missing translations
  $ rake translate:lost_in_translation LOCALE=nl
  - adding the missing keys to each yml file.

- copy the below locales yml to your new app
	- common
		gems/refinerycms-i18n-0.9.8.12/config/locales/zh-CN.yml
		(when create new app, copy it to the app_name/config/locales/)
	- engines
		(when create new app, copy it to the /vendor/refinerycms/xxx/config/locales/)
		- authentication
			gems/refinerycms-0.9.8.5/vendor/refinerycms/authentication/config/locales
		- core
			gems/refinerycms-0.9.8.5/vendor/refinerycms/core/config/locales/zh-CN.yml
		- dashboard
			gems/refinerycms-0.9.8.5/vendor/refinerycms/dashboard/config/locales
		- images
			gems/refinerycms-0.9.8.5/vendor/refinerycms/images/config/locales
		- pages
			gems/refinerycms-0.9.8.5/vendor/refinerycms/pages/config/locales
		- resources
			gems/refinerycms-0.9.8.5/vendor/refinerycms/resources/config/locales
		- settings
			gems/refinerycms-0.9.8.5/vendor/refinerycms/settings/config/locales
		- inquiries
			gems/refinerycms-inquiries-0.9.8.10/config/locales
		- news
			gems/refinerycms-news-0.9.9.6/config/locales
		- blog
			gems/refinerycms-blog-1.0.rc16/config/locales